<usermanual>
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

						THE NEED FOR COGNITION SCALE - 18 item format
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

Script Author: Katja Borchert, Ph.D. (katjab@millisecond.com) for Millisecond Software, LLC
Date: 11-08-2012
last updated:  02-25-2022 by K. Borchert (katjab@millisecond.com) for Millisecond Software, LLC

Script Copyright © 02-25-2022 Millisecond Software

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
BACKGROUND INFO 	
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

This script implements the 18 item Need for Cognition Scale by
 
Cacioppo,J.T., Petty,R.E. & Kao, C.F (1984). The efficient assessment of need for cognition. Journal of 
Personality Assessment, 48, 306-307.

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
OVERVIEW
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
participant works on 18 9-point Likert questions. Each question has 9 answer choices, ranging from very strong
agreement to very strong disagreement.

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
DURATION 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
the default set-up of the script takes appr. 3 minutes to complete

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
DATA FILE INFORMATION 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
The default data stored in the data files are:

(1) Raw data file: 'NCS.iqdat'

date, time:						date and time script was run with the current group/subjectnumber 
subject, group, session:	  	with the current subject/groupnumber/session id
build:							the Inquisit build  

q*_response:					response given (in assigned values -> reversed scoring already taken into account for R questions)
								4 = very strong agreement
								-4 = very strong disagreement

q*_latency:						how much time (in ms) the participant spent on the surveypage with this particular question (the last time this particular surveypage was visited)


(2) Summary data file: 'needcognitionscale_summary*.iqdat'

inquisit.version:				Inquisit version run
computer.platform:				the platform the script was run on (win/mac/ios/android)
startDate:						date script was run
startTime:						time script was started
subjectid:						assigned subject id number
groupid:						assigned group id number
sessionid:						assigned session id number
elapsedTime:					time it took to run script (in ms); measured from onset to offset of script
completed:						0 = script was not completed (prematurely aborted); 
								1 = script was completed (all conditions run)

totalscore: 					sum of the 18 individual question scores, rated on a scale from -4 to +4 
								(Total Range: -72 to +72)
								
+ responses to all individual questions

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
QUESTIONNAIRE SET-UP
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
1) Questions:
18 9-point Likert questions total, 4 questions per page


2) Required Responses:
By default the answer to each question is required (Go to QUESTIONS and edit each individual
question)

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
INSTRUCTIONS 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
instructions for the questions are not originals; they can be changed under
VALUES-> EDITABLE PARAMETERS -> parameters.instructions

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
EDITABLE CODE 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
check below for (relatively) easily editable parameters, stimuli, instructions etc. 
Keep in mind that you can use this script as a template and therefore always "mess" with the entire code 
to further customize your experiment.

The parameters you can change are:

/instructions:			the wording used in instructions

</usermanual>


**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	EDITABLE PARAMETERS: change editable parameters here
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************

<parameters>
/instructions = "People differ in how much they engage in and enjoy thinking. Read each statement and click the appropriate response button. Do not spend too much time on any statement. Answer quickly and honestly.
"
</parameters>

**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	EDITABLE LISTS: change editable lists here
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************


**************************************************************************************************************
								!!!REMAINING CODE: Customize after careful consideration only!!!
**************************************************************************************************************


**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	DEFAULTS
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
script requires Inquisit 6.5.2.0 or higher

<defaults>
/canvasaspectratio = (4,3)
/minimumversion = "6.5.2.0"
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/txbgcolor = white
/ txcolor = (0, 0, 0)
</defaults>


**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	DATA
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************

Note: data file explanations under User Manual Information at the top

********************
raw data
********************

The raw questionnaire data are saved under "NCS.iqdat"

********************
summary data
********************

<summarydata>
/columns = (inquisit.version, computer.platform,script.startDate, script.startTime, script.subjectId, script.groupId, script.sessionId, script.elapsedTime, 
script.completed, expressions.totalscore, 
radiobuttons.q1.response, radiobuttons.q2.response, radiobuttons.q3R.response, radiobuttons.q4R.response, 
radiobuttons.q5R.response, radiobuttons.q6.response, radiobuttons.q7R.response, radiobuttons.q8R.response, 
radiobuttons.q9R.response, radiobuttons.q10.response, radiobuttons.q11.response, radiobuttons.q12R.response,
radiobuttons.q13.response, radiobuttons.q14.response, radiobuttons.q15.response, radiobuttons.q16R.response,
radiobuttons.q17R.response, radiobuttons.q18.response)
</summarydata>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	EXPRESSIONS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
totalscore:								holds the total of all scores 

<expressions>
/totalscore = 
radiobuttons.q1.response + radiobuttons.q2.response + radiobuttons.q3R.response + radiobuttons.q4R.response + 
radiobuttons.q5R.response + radiobuttons.q6.response + radiobuttons.q7R.response + radiobuttons.q8R.response +
radiobuttons.q9R.response + radiobuttons.q10.response + radiobuttons.q11.response + radiobuttons.q12R.response +
radiobuttons.q13.response + radiobuttons.q14.response + radiobuttons.q15.response + radiobuttons.q16R.response +
radiobuttons.q17R.response + radiobuttons.q18.response

</expressions>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	QUESTIONS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
<radiobuttons q1>
/caption = "1. I would prefer complex to simple problems"
/ options = ("very strong~nagreement", "strong~nagreement", "moderate~nagreement", "slight~nagreement", 
"neither~nagreement ~nnor~ndisagreement", "slight~ndisagreement", "moderate~ndisagreement  ", "strong~ndisagreement", "very strong~ndisagreement")
/required = true
/ optionvalues = ("4", "3", "2", "1", "0", "-1", "-2", "-3", "-4")
/ orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q2>
/caption = "2. I like to have the responsibility of handling a situation that requires a lot of thinking."
/ options = ("very strong~nagreement", "strong~nagreement", "moderate~nagreement", "slight~nagreement", 
"neither~nagreement ~nnor~ndisagreement", "slight~ndisagreement", "moderate~ndisagreement  ", "strong~ndisagreement", "very strong~ndisagreement")
/required = true
/ optionvalues = ("4", "3", "2", "1", "0", "-1", "-2", "-3", "-4")
/ orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q3R>
/caption = "3. Thinking is not my idea of fun."
/ options = ("very strong~nagreement", "strong~nagreement", "moderate~nagreement", "slight~nagreement", 
"neither~nagreement ~nnor~ndisagreement", "slight~ndisagreement", "moderate~ndisagreement  ", "strong~ndisagreement", "very strong~ndisagreement")
/required = true
/ optionvalues = ("-4", "-3", "-2", "-1", "0", "1", "2", "3", "4")
/ orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q4R>
/caption = "4. I would rather do something that requires little thought than something that is sure to challenge my thinking abilities."
/ options = ("very strong~nagreement", "strong~nagreement", "moderate~nagreement", "slight~nagreement", 
"neither~nagreement ~nnor~ndisagreement", "slight~ndisagreement", "moderate~ndisagreement  ", "strong~ndisagreement", "very strong~ndisagreement")
/required = true
/ optionvalues = ("-4", "-3", "-2", "-1", "0", "1", "2", "3", "4")
/ orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q5R>
/caption = "5. I try to anticipate and avoid situations where there is likely a chance I will have to think in depth about something."
/ options = ("very strong~nagreement", "strong~nagreement", "moderate~nagreement", "slight~nagreement", 
"neither~nagreement ~nnor~ndisagreement", "slight~ndisagreement", "moderate~ndisagreement  ", "strong~ndisagreement", "very strong~ndisagreement")
/required = true
/ optionvalues = ("-4", "-3", "-2", "-1", "0", "1", "2", "3", "4")
/ orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q6>
/caption = "6. I find satisfaction in deliberating hard and for long hours."
/ options = ("very strong~nagreement", "strong~nagreement", "moderate~nagreement", "slight~nagreement", 
"neither~nagreement ~nnor~ndisagreement", "slight~ndisagreement", "moderate~ndisagreement  ", "strong~ndisagreement", "very strong~ndisagreement")
/required = true
/ optionvalues = ("4", "3", "2", "1", "0", "-1", "-2", "-3", "-4")
/ orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q7R>
/caption = "7. I only think as hard as I have to"
/ options = ("very strong~nagreement", "strong~nagreement", "moderate~nagreement", "slight~nagreement", 
"neither~nagreement ~nnor~ndisagreement", "slight~ndisagreement", "moderate~ndisagreement  ", "strong~ndisagreement", "very strong~ndisagreement")
/required = true
/ optionvalues = ("-4", "-3", "-2", "-1", "0", "1", "2", "3", "4")
/ orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q8R>
/caption = "8. I prefer to think about small, daily projects to long-term ones."
/ options = ("very strong~nagreement", "strong~nagreement", "moderate~nagreement", "slight~nagreement", 
"neither~nagreement ~nnor~ndisagreement", "slight~ndisagreement", "moderate~ndisagreement  ", "strong~ndisagreement", "very strong~ndisagreement")
/required = true
/ optionvalues = ("-4", "-3", "-2", "-1", "0", "1", "2", "3", "4")
/ orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q9R>
/caption = "9. I like tasks that require little thought once I've learned them"
/ options = ("very strong~nagreement", "strong~nagreement", "moderate~nagreement", "slight~nagreement", 
"neither~nagreement ~nnor~ndisagreement", "slight~ndisagreement", "moderate~ndisagreement  ", "strong~ndisagreement", "very strong~ndisagreement")
/required = true
/ optionvalues = ("-4", "-3", "-2", "-1", "0", "1", "2", "3", "4")
/ orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q10>
/caption = "10. The idea of relying on thought to make my way to the top appeals to me"
/ options = ("very strong~nagreement", "strong~nagreement", "moderate~nagreement", "slight~nagreement", 
"neither~nagreement ~nnor~ndisagreement", "slight~ndisagreement", "moderate~ndisagreement  ", "strong~ndisagreement", "very strong~ndisagreement")
/required = true
/ optionvalues = ("4", "3", "2", "1", "0", "-1", "-2", "-3", "-4")
/ orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q11>
/caption = "11. I really enjoy a task that involves coming up with new solutions to problems."
/ options = ("very strong~nagreement", "strong~nagreement", "moderate~nagreement", "slight~nagreement", 
"neither~nagreement ~nnor~ndisagreement", "slight~ndisagreement", "moderate~ndisagreement  ", "strong~ndisagreement", "very strong~ndisagreement")
/required = true
/ optionvalues = ("4", "3", "2", "1", "0", "-1", "-2", "-3", "-4")
/ orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q12R>
/caption = "12. Learning new ways to think doesn't excite me very much."
/ options = ("very strong~nagreement", "strong~nagreement", "moderate~nagreement", "slight~nagreement", 
"neither~nagreement ~nnor~ndisagreement", "slight~ndisagreement", "moderate~ndisagreement  ", "strong~ndisagreement", "very strong~ndisagreement")
/required = true
/ optionvalues = ("-4", "-3", "-2", "-1", "0", "1", "2", "3", "4")
/ orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q13>
/caption = "13. I prefer my life to be filled with puzzles that I must solve."
/ options = ("very strong~nagreement", "strong~nagreement", "moderate~nagreement", "slight~nagreement", 
"neither~nagreement ~nnor~ndisagreement", "slight~ndisagreement", "moderate~ndisagreement  ", "strong~ndisagreement", "very strong~ndisagreement")
/required = true
/ optionvalues = ("4", "3", "2", "1", "0", "-1", "-2", "-3", "-4")
/ orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q14>
/caption = "14. The notion of thinking abstractly is appealing to me."
/ options = ("very strong~nagreement", "strong~nagreement", "moderate~nagreement", "slight~nagreement", 
"neither~nagreement ~nnor~ndisagreement", "slight~ndisagreement", "moderate~ndisagreement  ", "strong~ndisagreement", "very strong~ndisagreement")
/required = true
/ optionvalues = ("4", "3", "2", "1", "0", "-1", "-2", "-3", "-4")
/ orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q15>
/caption = "15. I would prefer a task that is intellectual, difficult, and important to one that is somewhat important but does not require much thought."
/ options = ("very strong~nagreement", "strong~nagreement", "moderate~nagreement", "slight~nagreement", 
"neither~nagreement ~nnor~ndisagreement", "slight~ndisagreement", "moderate~ndisagreement  ", "strong~ndisagreement", "very strong~ndisagreement")
/required = true
/ optionvalues = ("4", "3", "2", "1", "0", "-1", "-2", "-3", "-4")
/ orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q16R>
/caption = "16. I feel relief rather than satisfaction after completing a task that required a lot of mental effort."
/ options = ("very strong~nagreement", "strong~nagreement", "moderate~nagreement", "slight~nagreement", 
"neither~nagreement ~nnor~ndisagreement", "slight~ndisagreement", "moderate~ndisagreement  ", "strong~ndisagreement", "very strong~ndisagreement")
/required = true
/ optionvalues = ("-4", "-3", "-2", "-1", "0", "1", "2", "3", "4")
/ orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q17R>
/caption = "17. It's enough for me that something gets the job done; I don't care how or why it works."
/ options = ("very strong~nagreement", "strong~nagreement", "moderate~nagreement", "slight~nagreement", 
"neither~nagreement ~nnor~ndisagreement", "slight~ndisagreement", "moderate~ndisagreement  ", "strong~ndisagreement", "very strong~ndisagreement")
/required = true
/ optionvalues = ("-4", "-3", "-2", "-1", "0", "1", "2", "3", "4")
/ orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q18>
/caption = "18. I usually end up deliberating about issues even when they do not affect me personally."
/ options = ("very strong~nagreement", "strong~nagreement", "moderate~nagreement", "slight~nagreement", 
"neither~nagreement ~nnor~ndisagreement", "slight~ndisagreement", "moderate~ndisagreement  ", "strong~ndisagreement", "very strong~ndisagreement")
/required = true
/ optionvalues = ("4", "3", "2", "1", "0", "-1", "-2", "-3", "-4")
/ orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	SURVEYPAGES
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

<surveypage NCS1>
/ caption = "<%parameters.instructions%>"
/ questions = [1 = q1, q2]
</surveypage>

<surveypage NCS2>
/ caption = "<%parameters.instructions%>"
/ questions = [1 = q3R, q4R]
</surveypage>

<surveypage NCS3>
/ caption = "<%parameters.instructions%>"
/ questions = [1 = q5R, q6]
</surveypage>

<surveypage NCS4>
/ caption = "<%parameters.instructions%>"
/ questions = [1 = q7R, q8R]
</surveypage>

<surveypage NCS5>
/ caption = "<%parameters.instructions%>"
/ questions = [1 = q9R, q10]
/ showpagenumbers = false
</surveypage>

<surveypage NCS6>
/ caption = "<%parameters.instructions%>"
/ questions = [1 = q11, q12R]
/ showpagenumbers = false
</surveypage>

<surveypage NCS7>
/ caption = "<%parameters.instructions%>"
/ questions = [1 = q13, q14]
</surveypage>

<surveypage NCS8>
/ caption = "<%parameters.instructions%>"
/ questions = [1 = q15, q16R]
</surveypage>

<surveypage NCS9>
/ caption = "<%parameters.instructions%>"
/ questions = [1 = q17R, q18]
</surveypage>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	SURVEY
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

<survey NCS>
/ pages = [
	1 = NCS1; 
	2 = NCS2; 
	3 = NCS3; 
	4 = NCS4; 
	5 = NCS5;
	6 = NCS6;
	7 = NCS7;
	8 = NCS8;
	9 = NCS9;
]
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ subcaptionfontstyle = ("Arial", 1.5%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ itemfontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, true, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ responsefontstyle = ("Arial", 1.75%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ txcolor = (0, 0, 0)
/ showquestionnumbers = false
/ showpagenumbers = false
/ navigationbuttonfontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ navigationbuttonsize = (15%, 5%)
/ backbuttonposition = (20%, 90%)
/ nextbuttonposition = (70%, 90%)
/ finishlabel = "Finish"
</survey>

